body.description: Incorporate timeless grace into your bedroom with the Prepac Astrid 6 Drawer Dresser. A sturdy profiled top, clean lines, profiled drawer fronts and solid wood knobs amplify a contemporary design with a rich Espresso laminate finish, making this a perfect dresser for the bedroom. This double-column dresser houses six full-size drawers for clothes, running on smooth roller glides with built-in safety stops. This multi-drawer storage dresser is a space-saving clothes organizer for bedrooms, but it also acts as an excellent storage cabinet in your walk-in closet, living room, or entryway. The wide, flat top can serve as a TV stand or a display for lamps, electronics, picture frames, and more. Made from a non-toxic, CARB-2 compliant laminated composite wood, drawer sides constructed of solid pine and a sturdy back panel for reliable storage, this high-quality dresser ships flat packed and can be assembled in two hours or less. Measuring 16" D x 47.25" W x 28.25" H with each deep drawer measuring 13.5" D x 20.5" W x 4.5" H, this horizontal double drawer dresser is a must-have piece of bedroom furniture. Pair this all-purpose dresser with other items from the Astrid collection for a uniform bedroom set.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: this dresser is so cute i love. the assembly was kinda confusing in the beginning but once you understand it, it’s really easy ! came with a few chips in bit but has a marker that come with it for quick fix.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy and Great Value
reviews.reviewText: No, you are not getting a solid wood piece of furniture. You are looking at 4 figures minimum for that. This is engineered wood but had no issues upon assembly or daily use. This is easy to assemble and looks quite nice upon completion.If you notice gaps between the drawers and dresser, you have the drawer in wrong. It is very easy to do since the drawers slide so nicely whether they are in the track correctly or not. No need for a major change - just pull the drawer back out from the dresser and try inserting again. It may take a few times and give a few good laughs at your spouse.I purchased two for a walk-in closet due to the lower height sits a few inches below shirts on hangers and would buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: So the dresser is ok, it was easy to build by myself and the instructions were easy to follow. I will say the piece along the bottom on the front got damaged, I was not "man handling" it by any means, I put in the peg and put the board on top like it says to and the peg went straight through the front. I had to use spakel to try to fix it which you can see in the images. This dresser will not last a lifetime, but you get what you pay for. It matches the rest of my step daughters furniture and she likes it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I wouldn’t recommend. It’s not terrible but its DEFINITELY NOT worth the hassle. Putting it together took about 2hrs & a half. I hate the fact that you have to screw the bottom of the dressers in. It’s a lot but I wouldn’t recommend if you plan on stuffing he drawers. In other words the durability is a 2 in my opinion.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Decent final product, difficult to assemble
reviews.reviewText: Assembly was very difficult. Similar pieces were not labeled and I was left to more or less guess what orientation they were supposed to be in, resulting in some mistakes. Also, product had several scratches on it. They give you a sharpie to cover up the scratches in the original packaging so this seems like a common occurrence

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just what we needed
reviews.reviewText: We were looking for a specific type of dresser that would not break the bank.My 8 year old set this up with minimal adult supervision (adult was in the room since our 3 yo was in there and wanting to help). 3 year old helped with adult supervision ( child put the knobs on the drawer)drawers can be easily pulled out of the cubby since there isn’t hardware to stop it from fully coming out of the track/ cubby.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for price
reviews.reviewText: So as soon as I opened it, I realized the stabilizer piece (skinny piece in the front) was split right down the middle. I reached out to the manufacturer & they are able to ship out a replacement piece this week, even though the item came from Amazon’s warehouse! The manufacturer customer service was great. The product was very easy to put together & the instructions were super clear. It took maybe an hour for my husband & I to assemble!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I’m fairly mechanically inclined and it took me a solid 3 hours to assemble. This is probably too difficult to assemble for the average customer. Also, it’s very heavy (approx 75lbs) and therefore gets pretty beat up during shipping. Ours came with several deep scratches and a good sized chip. We are going to try to get a partial refund for the damage. Little chance yours will arrive without damage. If I had to do it over again I would spend a little more for a fully assembled dresser from a furniture store and have it delivered.

reviews.reviewTitle: Looks great and easy to assemble!
reviews.reviewText: This is a nice, modern and very sturdy dresser. Set up took about an hour for one person, using a power drill, and instructions were straight forward. Some reviews said drawers were not aligned, or that this was junk. Clearly they didn’t know what they were doing or didn’t follow instructions properly. Each drawer aligns perfectly! For $250, this a quality piece. Would definitely recommend!

Took some time to assemble, but a problem with some of the plastic drawer slider supports. These are thosewhich snapped into the dresser's vertical sides and center panel by means of their plastic studs fitting into pre-drilledholes. But when the flat-pack box was opened about twelve of these studs had broken off.As the weight of the drawers is supported by these supports, without the studs there is no way to fit thesupport the drawers. Glue or adhesive was insufficient, and I had to screw the supports into place.The packing was strong and well put together but the sliders were on the bottom end and must havebeen damaged during shipping.Problem: We really need three slider supports, but how do I go about ordering them as there does notappear to be a feedback link, or none I can find.Any help?
Bought this for my nursery. Easy to assemble, clean look and has lots of space for all my little ones things!
This dresser lasted us three years. But there was an industrial type of smell that came off of it and only in the past year has faded.
